<HL>
   Letters to the Editor:
   The Language Barrier
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<CO>
   CANDA
</CO>
<LP>
   As Premier Robert Bourassa points out (Americas column,
op-ed page, Aug. 17), currently high interest rates are not
helping small business in Quebec. But another big factor not
even mentioned is the province's continuing xenophobic
intolerance of the English language. The welcome mat says
"bienvenue" but something's getting lost in the translation.
   Gary A. Lyon
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Westfield, N.J.
</TEXT>
